citeinfo.title: San Diego County, California land parcels, 2009

descript.abstract: Land parcels in San Diego County, California, 2009.
descript.purpose: Data is generalized and created for use in regional projects.
descript.supplinf: Please acknowledge SanGIS as a source when SanGIS data is used in the preparation of reports, papers, publications, maps, and other products. Parcel Zone and Land Use codes are used by County appraisers. They are not well maintained and are not considered reliable for other purposes. Please use the landuse layer for this information (supplied to SanGIS by SANDAG). Use the zoning layer for zoning in the County unincorporated areas. Contact the appropriate city for other zoning information. Most of the parcel attributes are joined to SanGIS graphics from County Assessor files. SanGIS does not enter ownership information. If you detect errors in the attributes, we can pass those along to the County Assessor but SanGIS cannot make the changes. Note from SanGIS: The parcel layers now include condominium records. If you use the identify tool on a condo polygon you will see multiple ownership records displayed for the condo owners. The parcels are also now multi-part. If a parcel is split by a right-of-way for example, the two parts are linked and share attributes. SanGIS notes that the original source is COGO which is a computer program that is used to calculate coordinate geometry. It is used to solve the geometric problems encountered in civil engineering applications including: property boundary and right of way surveys highway and interchange design construction layout bridge geometry
